## Example 4 — Multiply and Divide Polynomial Expressions

A manufacturer compares the areas of two rectangular planters:

`(x^2 + 15x + 50) / (x + 2)`

and

`(x^2 + 30x + 200) / (x + 2)`

Write and simplify the ratio of the first area to the second.

Set up the ratio:

`((x^2 + 15x + 50)/(x + 2)) / ((x^2 + 30x + 200)/(x + 2))`

Factor:

* `x^2 + 15x + 50 = (x + 5)(x + 10)`
* `x^2 + 30x + 200 = (x + 10)(x + 20)`

Simplify:

`(x + 5) / (x + 20)`

