## Example 5 — Simplify Complex Fractions

Simplify

`(3x / (x - y)) / (6xy / (4x^2 - 4y^2))`

Rewrite as division, multiply by the reciprocal, factor, and simplify:

`(3x / (x - y)) * ((4x^2 - 4y^2) / 6xy)`

`= (3x / (x - y)) * (4(x + y)(x - y) / 6xy)`

`= 2(x + y) / y`

## Talk About It

If you simplify a ratio of two rational expressions that both contain polynomials in their numerators and denominators, will the simplified expression always, sometimes, or never still be a rational expression with polynomials? Explain.

